{
  "stem": "14168.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they figured that was the end of everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And actually, I would say, the dream or the illusion, which German Jews had that they had been emancipated, collapsed overnight.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- it-- it turned out that they had lived in a fool's paradise.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I still remember, there was a Jewish-- the Zionist paper, the which came out with a wonderful, wonderful issue on the 1st of April. 'Wear it with pride, the yellow badge.' [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they reminded the Jews that they needn't be afraid of anything, that they had a long history of suffering, and that this was another test to which they were put, and admonished them to help the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Israel, or what was then Palestine, the reconstruction, the building of a Jewish home in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 92
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I must say I had been-- before 1933, I always thought, like my parents and most German Jews, we were Germans of the Jewish faith.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we were Germans.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because we-- after all, my uncles, my father, and my-- one of my great-grandfathers had fought in the German army.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they had shown as much bravery as everybody else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But that was of no avail.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remember reading the by Theodor Herzl, years before this happened, written years before that happened.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And a very interesting book, by one Dr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Leo Pinsker-- P-I-N-S-K-E-R-- written in 1882, predicted exactly what would happen, if the Jews in Germany and in the other Western countries persisted in their dream of being-- of a symbiosis.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that came to a shattering end.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I-- as a matter of fact, I completely changed my view, my-- I would almost say identity as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I felt that I was a Jew not only religiously but ethnically.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
